<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd" []>
<concept xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="dita-custom-content" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:concept.xsd:1.1">
  <title>DITA Custom Content</title>
  <conbody>
    <p conref="custom-content-customization.xml#custom-content/custom-content-definition"/>
    <p>You can insert custom content by means of:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p><uicontrol>Custom Content</uicontrol> toolbar.</p>
        <image href="custom-content-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Custom Content</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> menu.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Hot keys.</p>
        <p><note>
            <p>To see the list of available custom content and associated hot-keys for the current document, click the <uicontrol>Edit Custom Content</uicontrol> button <image href="edit-custom-content-button.png" align="center"/>on the toolbar.</p>
            <fig>
              <title>Edit Custom Content Dialog.</title>
              <image href="edit-custom-content-dialog-dita.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
            </fig>
          </note></p>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p id="dita-custom-content-intro">You can use DITA custom content to quickly  insert the most common DITA content portions. DITA custom content differs from Docbook custom content.</p>
    <p>In DITA topics, you can insert the following pre-defined custom content templates:<ol>
        <li>
          <p><b>Set Bold</b></p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;b&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Set Underline</b></p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;u&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Set Italic</b></p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;i&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Graphic</b></p>
          <p>Asks you to browse for a file and inserts inline <codeph>&lt;image&gt;</codeph>, or <codeph>&lt;title&gt;</codeph>+<codeph>&lt;image&gt;</codeph>, depending on the cursor position.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Enumerated List Item</b></p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;ol&gt;</codeph>+<codeph>&lt;li&gt;</codeph>, or just <codeph>&lt;li&gt;</codeph>, depending on the cursor position.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Itemized List Item</b></p>
          <p>Insets <codeph>&lt;ul&gt;</codeph>+<codeph>&lt;li&gt;</codeph>, or just <codeph>&lt;li&gt;</codeph>, depending on the cursor position.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Para</b></p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;p&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Note</b></p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;note&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Section</b></p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;section&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Step</b> (in <xref href="task.xml">tasks</xref> only)</p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;step&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Info</b> (in <xref href="task.xml">tasks</xref> only)</p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;info&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Task</b> (in <xref href="task.xml">tasks</xref> and <xref href="composite.xml">composites</xref> only)</p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;task&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Concept</b> (in <xref href="concept.xml">concepts</xref> and <xref href="composite.xml">composites</xref> only)</p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;concept&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Topic</b> (in <xref href="generic-topic.xml">generic topics</xref> and <xref href="composite.xml">composites</xref> only)</p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;topic&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Insert Reference</b> (in <xref href="reference.xml">references</xref> and <xref href="composite.xml">composites</xref> only)</p>
          <p>Inserts <codeph>&lt;reference&gt;</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
      </ol></p>
  </conbody>
  <related-links>
    <link href="custom-content-customization.xml"/>
  </related-links>
</concept>
